#### API Summary

The following operations are for user statistics:

* [ReadAllUserStats](#capi-playerstats-readalluserstats) - returns the complete list of user stats
* [ReadUserStatsSubset](#capi-playerstats-readuserstatssubset) - returns a specified stats to the client
* [ReadUserStatsForCategory](#capi-playerstats-readuserstatsforcategory) - returns the specified category of stats to the client
* [IncrementUserStats](#capi-playerstats-incrementuserstats) - perform increment/decrement operations on the statistics
* [ProcessStatistics](#capi-playerstats-processstatistics) - perform operations on the statistics according to the <a href="#" onclick='window.navigateToTarget("#appendix-statisticsgrammar");'>stats grammar</a>.
* [ResetAllUserStats](#capi-playerstats-resetalluserstats) - resets all user statistics to their initial values (as defined by their rules).  Useful for debugging.

The following operations are specific to the XP system:

* [IncrementExperiencePoints](#capi-playerstats-incrementexperiencepoints) – award XP to the user
* [GetNextExperienceLevel](#capi-playerstats-getnextexperiencelevel) – returns information about the next experience level, including associated rewards
* [SetExperiencePoints](#capi-playerstats-setexperiencepoints) - used to specifically set XP (useful for debugging).  Does not generate any associated rewards for levelling-up

